  "text": "where is the dielectric constant that represents the energy stored in the material when exposed to an external electric-field and symbolizes the dielectric loss as given in (2) for the total absorbed energy due the ionic conduction and dipole rotation loss mechanisms. The ratio between dissipated and stored energy is the loss tangent tanδ [CITATION_1] .",
